{"paragraphs":[{"cues":[{"time":1000,"text":"So, can we dare to be optimistic?"},{"time":4000,"text":"Well, the thesis of \"The Bottom Billion\""},{"time":5000,"text":"is that a billion people have been stuck living"},{"time":10000,"text":"in economies that have been stagnant for 40 years,"},{"time":15000,"text":"and hence diverging from the rest of mankind."},{"time":19000,"text":"And so, the real question to pose is not, \"Can we be optimistic?\""},{"time":22000,"text":"It's, \"How can we give credible hope to that billion people?\""},{"time":27000,"text":"That, to my mind, is the fundamental challenge now of development."}]},{"cues":[{"time":33000,"text":"What I'm going to offer you is a recipe,"},{"time":36000,"text":"a combination of the two forces that changed the world for good,"},{"time":41000,"text":"which is the alliance of compassion and enlightened self-interest."},{"time":48000,"text":"Compassion, because a billion people are living in societies"},{"time":53000,"text":"that have not offered credible hope."},{"time":58000,"text":"That is a human tragedy."},{"time":61000,"text":"Enlightened self-interest, because if that economic divergence"},{"time":66000,"text":"continues for another 40 years,"},{"time":71000,"text":"combined with social integration globally,"},{"time":75000,"text":"it will build a nightmare for our children."},{"time":79000,"text":"We need compassion to get ourselves started,"},{"time":83000,"text":"and enlightened self-interest to get ourselves serious."},{"time":89000,"text":"That's the alliance that changes the world."}]},{"cues":[{"time":92000,"text":"So, what does it mean to get serious about providing hope for the bottom billion?"},{"time":99000,"text":"What can we actually do?"},{"time":103000,"text":"Well, a good guide is to think,"},{"time":106000,"text":"\"What did we do last time the rich world got serious"},{"time":111000,"text":"about developing another region of the world?\""},{"time":115000,"text":"That gives us, it turns out, quite a good clue,"},{"time":119000,"text":"except you have to go back quite a long time."},{"time":122000,"text":"The last time the rich world got serious"},{"time":124000,"text":"about developing another region was in the late 1940s."},{"time":130000,"text":"The rich world was you, America,"},{"time":135000,"text":"and the region that needed to be developed was my world, Europe."},{"time":140000,"text":"That was post-War Europe."}]},{"cues":[{"time":143000,"text":"Why did America get serious?"},{"time":146000,"text":"It wasn't just compassion for Europe, though there was that."},{"time":150000,"text":"It was that you knew you had to,"},{"time":153000,"text":"because, in the late 1940s, country after country in Central Europe"},{"time":158000,"text":"was falling into the Soviet bloc, and so you knew you'd no choice."},{"time":164000,"text":"Europe had to be dragged into economic development."}]},{"cues":[{"time":167000,"text":"So, what did you do, last time you got serious?"},{"time":171000,"text":"Well, yes, you had a big aid program. Thank you very much."},{"time":175000,"text":"That was Marshall aid: we need to do it again. Aid is part of the solution."},{"time":180000,"text":"But what else did you do?"},{"time":183000,"text":"Well, you tore up your trade policy, and totally reversed it."},{"time":190000,"text":"Before the war, America had been highly protectionist."},{"time":194000,"text":"After the war, you opened your markets to Europe,"},{"time":198000,"text":"you dragged Europe into the then-global economy, which was your economy,"},{"time":202000,"text":"and you institutionalized that trade liberalization"},{"time":204000,"text":"through founding the General Agreement on Tariffs and Trade."},{"time":208000,"text":"So, total reversal of trade policy."}]},{"cues":[{"time":211000,"text":"Did you do anything else?"},{"time":212000,"text":"Yes, you totally reversed your security policy."},{"time":215000,"text":"Before the war, your security policy had been isolationist."},{"time":219000,"text":"After the war, you tear that up, you put 100,000 troops in Europe"},{"time":225000,"text":"for over 40 years."},{"time":227000,"text":"So, total reversal of security policy. Anything else?"},{"time":232000,"text":"Yes, you tear up the \"Eleventh Commandment\" --"},{"time":236000,"text":"national sovereignty."},{"time":239000,"text":"Before the war, you treated national sovereignty as so sacrosanct"},{"time":244000,"text":"that you weren't even willing to join the League of Nations."},{"time":247000,"text":"After the war, you found the United Nations,"},{"time":250000,"text":"you found the Organization for Economic Cooperation and Development,"},{"time":254000,"text":"you found the IMF, you encouraged Europe to create the European Community --"},{"time":259000,"text":"all systems for mutual government support."},{"time":263000,"text":"That is still the waterfront of effective policies:"},{"time":269000,"text":"aid, trade, security, governments."},{"time":273000,"text":"Of course, the details of policy are going to be different,"},{"time":276000,"text":"because the challenge is different."},{"time":278000,"text":"It's not rebuilding Europe, it's reversing the divergence"},{"time":284000,"text":"for the bottom billion, so that they actually catch up."},{"time":287000,"text":"Is that easier or harder?"},{"time":291000,"text":"We need to be at least as serious as we were then."}]},{"cues":[{"time":296000,"text":"Now, today I'm going to take just one of those four."},{"time":301000,"text":"I'm going to take the one that sounds the weakest,"},{"time":304000,"text":"the one that's just motherhood and apple pie --"},{"time":307000,"text":"governments, mutual systems of support for governments --"},{"time":310000,"text":"and I'm going to show you one idea"},{"time":314000,"text":"in how we could do something to strengthen governance,"},{"time":319000,"text":"and I'm going to show you that that is enormously important now."},{"time":326000,"text":"The opportunity we're going to look to"},{"time":331000,"text":"is a genuine basis for optimism about the bottom billion,"},{"time":337000,"text":"and that is the commodity booms."},{"time":340000,"text":"The commodity booms are pumping unprecedented amounts of money"},{"time":346000,"text":"into many, though not all, of the countries of the bottom billion."},{"time":352000,"text":"Partly, they're pumping money in because commodity prices are high,"},{"time":356000,"text":"but it's not just that. There's also a range of new discoveries."},{"time":363000,"text":"Uganda has just discovered oil, in about the most disastrous location on Earth;"},{"time":369000,"text":"Ghana has discovered oil;"},{"time":371000,"text":"Guinea has got a huge new exploitation of iron ore coming out of the ground."},{"time":376000,"text":"So, a mass of new discoveries."},{"time":379000,"text":"Between them, these new revenue flows dwarf aid."},{"time":384000,"text":"Just to give you one example:"},{"time":387000,"text":"Angola alone is getting 50 billion dollars a year in oil revenue."},{"time":392000,"text":"The entire aid flows to the 60 countries of the bottom billion last year were 34 billion."},{"time":398000,"text":"So, the flow of resources from the commodity booms"},{"time":403000,"text":"to the bottom billion are without precedent."},{"time":408000,"text":"So there's the optimism."}]},{"cues":[{"time":410000,"text":"The question is, how is it going to help their development?"},{"time":414000,"text":"It's a huge opportunity for transformational development."},{"time":418000,"text":"Will it be taken?"},{"time":420000,"text":"So, here comes a bit of science, and this is a bit of science I've done"},{"time":424000,"text":"since \"The Bottom Billion,\" so it's new."},{"time":427000,"text":"I've looked to see what is the relationship between"},{"time":431000,"text":"higher commodity prices of exports,"},{"time":434000,"text":"and the growth of commodity-exporting countries."},{"time":436000,"text":"And I've looked globally, I've taken all the countries in the world"},{"time":439000,"text":"for the last 40 years,"},{"time":441000,"text":"and looked to see what the relationship is."},{"time":444000,"text":"And the short run -- say, the first five to seven years -- is just great."},{"time":453000,"text":"In fact, it's hunky dory: everything goes up."},{"time":458000,"text":"You get more money because your terms of trade have improved,"},{"time":460000,"text":"but also that drives up output across the board."},{"time":463000,"text":"So GDP goes up a lot -- fantastic! That's the short run."},{"time":469000,"text":"And how about the long run?"},{"time":471000,"text":"Come back 15 years later."},{"time":474000,"text":"Well, the short run, it's hunky dory,"},{"time":476000,"text":"but the long run, it's humpty dumpty."},{"time":481000,"text":"You go up in the short run, but then most societies"},{"time":485000,"text":"historically have ended up worse than if they'd had no booms at all."},{"time":490000,"text":"That is not a forecast about how commodity prices go;"},{"time":494000,"text":"it's a forecast of the consequences, the long-term consequences,"},{"time":498000,"text":"for growth of an increase in prices."}]},{"cues":[{"time":503000,"text":"So, what goes wrong? Why is there this \"resource curse,\" as it's called?"},{"time":508000,"text":"And again, I've looked at that, and it turns out"},{"time":511000,"text":"that the critical issue is the level of governance,"},{"time":515000,"text":"the initial level of economic governance,"},{"time":517000,"text":"when the resource booms accrue."},{"time":520000,"text":"In fact, if you've got good enough governance,"},{"time":522000,"text":"there is no resource boom."},{"time":524000,"text":"You go up in the short term, and then you go up even more in the long term."},{"time":529000,"text":"That's Norway, the richest country in Europe. It's Australia. It's Canada."},{"time":535000,"text":"The resource curse is entirely confined to countries"},{"time":537000,"text":"below a threshold of governance."},{"time":539000,"text":"They still go up in the short run."},{"time":541000,"text":"That's what we're seeing across the bottom billion at the moment."},{"time":545000,"text":"The best growth rates they've had -- ever."},{"time":548000,"text":"And the question is whether the short run will persist."},{"time":554000,"text":"And with bad governance historically, over the last 40 years, it hasn't."},{"time":558000,"text":"It's countries like Nigeria, which are worse off than if they'd never had oil."}]},{"cues":[{"time":566000,"text":"So, there's a threshold level above which you go up in the long term,"},{"time":571000,"text":"and below which you go down."},{"time":573000,"text":"Just to benchmark that threshold,"},{"time":575000,"text":"it's about the governance level of Portugal in the mid 1980s."},{"time":582000,"text":"So, the question is, are the bottom billion above or below that threshold?"},{"time":587000,"text":"Now, there's one big change since the commodity booms of the 1970s,"},{"time":592000,"text":"and that is the spread of democracy."},{"time":595000,"text":"So I thought, well, maybe that is the thing"},{"time":597000,"text":"which has transformed governance in the bottom billion."},{"time":599000,"text":"Maybe we can be more optimistic because of the spread of democracy."},{"time":603000,"text":"So, I looked. Democracy does have significant effects --"},{"time":608000,"text":"and unfortunately, they're adverse."},{"time":611000,"text":"Democracies make even more of a mess of these resource booms than autocracies."}]},{"cues":[{"time":617000,"text":"At that stage I just wanted to abandon the research, but --"},{"time":620000,"text":"(Laughter)"},{"time":622000,"text":"-- it turns out that democracy is a little bit more complicated than that."},{"time":625000,"text":"Because there are two distinct aspects of democracy:"},{"time":629000,"text":"there's electoral competition, which determines how you acquire power,"},{"time":634000,"text":"and there are checks and balances, which determine how you use power."},{"time":640000,"text":"It turns out that electoral competition is the thing"},{"time":642000,"text":"that's doing the damage with democracy,"},{"time":644000,"text":"whereas strong checks and balances make resource booms good."},{"time":649000,"text":"And so, what the countries of the bottom billion need"},{"time":652000,"text":"is very strong checks and balances."},{"time":654000,"text":"They haven't got them."},{"time":656000,"text":"They got instant democracy in the 1990s:"},{"time":659000,"text":"elections without checks and balances."}]},{"cues":[{"time":662000,"text":"How can we help improve governance and introduce checks and balances?"},{"time":668000,"text":"In all the societies of the bottom billion,"},{"time":670000,"text":"there are intense struggles to do just that."},{"time":675000,"text":"The simple proposal is that we should have some international standards,"},{"time":680000,"text":"which will be voluntary, but which would spell out the key decision points"},{"time":685000,"text":"that need to be taken in order"},{"time":688000,"text":"to harness these resource revenues."},{"time":691000,"text":"We know these international standards work"},{"time":693000,"text":"because we've already got one."},{"time":695000,"text":"It's called the Extractive Industries Transparency Initiative."},{"time":698000,"text":"That is the very simple idea that governments should report"},{"time":703000,"text":"to their citizens what revenues they have."},{"time":706000,"text":"No sooner was it proposed"},{"time":708000,"text":"than reformers in Nigeria adopted it, pushed it and published the revenues in the paper."},{"time":715000,"text":"Nigerian newspapers circulations spiked."},{"time":717000,"text":"People wanted to know what their government was getting"},{"time":720000,"text":"in terms of revenue."}]},{"cues":[{"time":723000,"text":"So, we know it works. What would the content be of these international standards?"},{"time":730000,"text":"I can't go through all of them, but I'll give you an example."},{"time":735000,"text":"The first is how to take the resources out of the ground --"},{"time":739000,"text":"the economic processes, taking the resources out of the ground"},{"time":742000,"text":"and putting assets on top of the ground."},{"time":745000,"text":"And the first step in that is selling the rights to resource extraction."},{"time":749000,"text":"You know how rights to resource extraction are being sold at the moment,"},{"time":753000,"text":"how they've been sold over the last 40 years?"},{"time":755000,"text":"A company flies in, does a deal with a minister."},{"time":759000,"text":"And that's great for the company,"},{"time":761000,"text":"and it's quite often great for the minister --"},{"time":763000,"text":"(Laughter)"},{"time":764000,"text":"-- and it's not great for their country."},{"time":767000,"text":"There's a very simple institutional technology"},{"time":769000,"text":"which can transform that,"},{"time":771000,"text":"and it's called verified auctions."},{"time":776000,"text":"The public agency with the greatest expertise on Earth"},{"time":782000,"text":"is of course the treasury -- that is, the British Treasury."},{"time":785000,"text":"And the British Treasury decided that it would sell the rights"},{"time":788000,"text":"to third-generation mobile phones"},{"time":790000,"text":"by working out what those rights were worth."},{"time":793000,"text":"They worked out they were worth two billion pounds."},{"time":796000,"text":"Just in time, a set of economists got there and said,"},{"time":799000,"text":"\"Why not try an auction? It'll reveal the value.\""},{"time":802000,"text":"It went for 20 billion pounds through auction."},{"time":806000,"text":"If the British Treasury can be out by a factor of 10,"},{"time":809000,"text":"think what the ministry of finance in Sierra Leone is going to be like."},{"time":812000,"text":"(Laughter)"},{"time":813000,"text":"When I put that to the President of Sierra Leone,"},{"time":815000,"text":"the next day he asked the World Bank to send him a team"},{"time":818000,"text":"to give expertise on how to conduct auctions."}]},{"cues":[{"time":823000,"text":"There are five such decision points;"},{"time":825000,"text":"each one needs an international standard."},{"time":829000,"text":"If we could do it, we would change the world."},{"time":833000,"text":"We would be helping the reformers in these societies,"},{"time":837000,"text":"who are struggling for change."},{"time":840000,"text":"That's our modest role. We cannot change these societies,"},{"time":844000,"text":"but we can help the people in these societies"},{"time":847000,"text":"who are struggling and usually failing,"},{"time":850000,"text":"because the odds are so stacked against them."},{"time":856000,"text":"And yet, we've not got these rules."},{"time":859000,"text":"If you think about it, the cost of promulgating international rules"},{"time":863000,"text":"is zilch -- nothing."},{"time":866000,"text":"Why on Earth are they not there?"},{"time":870000,"text":"I realized that the reason they're not there"},{"time":874000,"text":"is that until we have a critical mass of informed citizens in our own societies,"},{"time":880000,"text":"politicians will get away with gestures."},{"time":883000,"text":"That unless we have an informed society,"},{"time":888000,"text":"what politicians do, especially in relation to Africa, is gestures:"},{"time":894000,"text":"things that look good, but don't work."},{"time":897000,"text":"And so I realized we had to go through the business"},{"time":900000,"text":"of building an informed citizenry."}]},{"cues":[{"time":904000,"text":"That's why I broke all the professional rules of conduct for an economist,"},{"time":909000,"text":"and I wrote an economics book that you could read on a beach."},{"time":912000,"text":"(Laughter)."},{"time":917000,"text":"However, I have to say, the process of communication"},{"time":921000,"text":"does not come naturally to me."},{"time":923000,"text":"This is why I'm on this stage, but it's alarming."},{"time":927000,"text":"I grew up in a culture of self-effacement."},{"time":935000,"text":"My wife showed me a blog comment on one of my last talks,"},{"time":939000,"text":"and the blog comment said, \"Collier is not charismatic --"},{"time":945000,"text":"(Laughter)"},{"time":948000,"text":"-- but his arguments are compelling.\""},{"time":951000,"text":"(Laughter)"},{"time":955000,"text":"(Applause)"},{"time":962000,"text":"If you agree with that sentiment,"},{"time":965000,"text":"and if you agree that we need a critical mass of informed citizenry,"},{"time":971000,"text":"you will realize that I need you."},{"time":975000,"text":"Please, become ambassadors."},{"time":977000,"text":"Thank you."},{"time":979000,"text":"(Applause)"}]}]}